---
title: Fajita-Spiced Chicken Bulgur Bowls with Tomato, Pickled Jalapeño & Creamy Salsa Verde
description: We love to end a day with a hearty meal that balances delicious flavors and enticing textures all in one satisfying bowl. You’ll top a base of scallion, tomato, and jalapeño-studded bulgur wheat with juicy fajita-spiced pork chops, and drizzle it all with homemade creamy salsa verde. Finish with a sprinkle of crisp sliced scallions and tangy pickled jalapeño, then curl up in your fave spot and prepare to be bowled over!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/fajita-spiced-pork-chop-bulgur-bowls-39175014.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64f8cbdda45bcf210b3b2a72.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/fajita-spiced-chicken-bulgur-bowls-64f8cbdda45bcf210b3b2a72
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Latin
nutrition:
  calories: 550 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 45 g
  sugar: 4 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 410 mg
---

Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}; reserve a pinch in a #small bowl{} (you'll use it in Step 5). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens. Thinly slice @jalapeño{1%unit} into rounds, removing ribs and seeds for less heat; mince a few rounds until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4 servings). Zest and quarter @lime{1%unit}. Dice @tomato{1%unit} into ½-inch pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium heat. Add scallion whites, remaining garlic, and ½ tsp @fajita spice blend{1%tbsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings). Cook, stirring, until softened and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @bulgur wheat{1/2%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, 1 cup water (2 cups for 4), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until water is absorbed and bulgur is tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

In a second #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced jalapeño, juice from half the lime (whole lime for 4 servings), @sugar{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4), and a pinch of @salt{}. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{30%seconds}. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with remaining Fajita Spice Blend, salt, and @pepper{}.

> Swap in chicken or steak for pork. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook steak to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

To #bowl{} with reserved garlic, add @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, a squeeze of lime juice (two squeezes for 4 servings), a big pinch of lime zest, and a pinch of minced jalapeño to taste.

> TIP: If you like some zesty heat, add a small splash of jalapeño pickling liquid in place of, or in addition to, lime juice.

Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff bulgur with a #fork{}. Stir in tomato, half the scallion greens, remaining lime zest, a squeeze of lime juice, and as much remaining minced jalapeño as you like. Season with salt and pepper. Thinly slice pork crosswise.

> Thinly slice chicken or steak against the grain.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Divide bulgur between shallow #bowls{}; top with pork. Drizzle everything with crema; garnish with remaining scallion greens and as much pickled jalapeño (draining first) as you like. Serve.